---
title: "bid (AuctionBidder)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_load: auction = s_auction, assetOut = auction.getAssetOut()
    q_load --> q_check_solution: check solution.length
    q_check_solution --> q_encode_calls: solution.length > 0
    q_encode_calls --> q_call_bid: data = abi.encode(solution)
    q_check_solution --> q_approve: solution.length == 0
    q_approve --> q_call_bid: forceApprove(assetOut, auction, getAssetOutAmount)
    q_call_bid --> q_check_leftover: auction.bid(assetIn, amount, data)
    q_check_leftover --> q_check_receiver: assetOutBalance > 0
    q_check_leftover --> [*]: assetOutBalance == 0
    q_check_receiver --> q_transfer: receiver != address(0)
    q_transfer --> [*]: safeTransfer(assetOut, receiver, balance)
    q_check_receiver --> [*]: receiver == address(0)

    note right of q_call_bid
        INV-001: If solution provided, callback mechanism is used for custom solve logic
        INV-002: If no solution, pre-approves exact assetOut amount needed
        INV-003: Leftover assetOut is forwarded to configured receiver
        INV-004: Caller must have AUCTION_BIDDER_ROLE
    end note
